2
00:00:35.035 --> 00:00:37.746
<i>Man. thought you'd be</i>
<i>off the clock by five.</i>

3
00:00:37.829 --> 00:00:40.707
<i>Did they keep you on call? Shit luck.</i>

4
00:00:41.291 --> 00:00:43.042
{\an8}<i>Cap said I could leave</i>
<i>my gun and badge</i>

5
00:00:43.126 --> 00:00:45.044
{\an8}<i>if I went home to listen to my old lady</i>

6
00:00:45.128 --> 00:00:50.091
{\an8}<i>go on and on about her online shopping</i>
<i>or whatever the hell she did all day.</i>

7
00:00:50.175 --> 00:00:52.969
<i>That’s what you get</i>
<i>for choosing the life of a public servant.</i>

8
00:00:53.052 --> 00:00:55.430
<i>It just had to fucking rain.</i>

9
00:00:55.513 --> 00:00:58.099
Hmm? What the hell you doin'? Back it up.

10
00:00:58.183 --> 00:00:59.267
Looking to get shot?

11
00:01:01.978 --> 00:01:04.647
{\an8}

12
00:01:25.877 --> 00:01:28.171
Got us a Cyberpsycho!

13
00:01:28.838 --> 00:01:30.673
Raise MaxTac now!

14
00:02:26.187 --> 00:02:27.856
Need to fry his system fast.

15
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:30.108
Freak's sporting military-grade ICE.

16
00:02:30.191 --> 00:02:32.819
Meaning that our tech isn't? Get to it!

17
00:03:08.479 --> 00:03:11.357
Fuck!

18
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:17.280
<i>So. what do you think?</i>

19
00:03:17.906 --> 00:03:20.283
<i>Still warm. that. Couple hours old.</i>

20
00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:22.493
<i>Lifted from the edgerunner</i>
<i>who scrolled it.</i>

21
00:03:22.577 --> 00:03:24.245
<i>Straight off the street.</i>

22
00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:25.747
So whacked!

23
00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:29.125
Doc. hey. you gotta tell me
who keeps feeding you these nuggets.

24
00:03:29.208 --> 00:03:30.585
<i>Kurosaki. Who else?</i>

25
00:03:30.668 --> 00:03:33.755
<i>Ain't no other editor who churns out</i>
<i>BDs that sweet and preem.</i>

26
00:03:33.838 --> 00:03:36.090
<i>Won't pull nothin' like that</i>
<i>off the shelf. neither.</i>

27
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:39.260
No shit. Brain's still buzzing.
Gonna be sick.

28
00:03:39.344 --> 00:03:41.346
<i>Slow. deep breaths. choom.</i>

29
00:03:41.429 --> 00:03:44.098
<i>Just left the head</i>
<i>of a skezzed-out chrome junkie.</i>

30
00:03:44.182 --> 00:03:46.100
<i>Cyberpsychosis ain't no joke.</i>

31
00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:49.312
<i>Anyway. either hurl or don't.</i>
<i>got more chips for you to slot.</i>

32
00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:50.772
Really? What?

33
00:03:50.855 --> 00:03:53.024
<i>Something special.</i>

34
00:03:54.275 --> 00:03:56.778
Huh? Cut the shit. man!

35
00:04:07.038 --> 00:04:10.458
Huh?

36
00:04:10.541 --> 00:04:13.378
<i>Cycle suspended</i>
<i>due to insufficient funds.</i>

37
00:04:13.461 --> 00:04:16.464
- Geez. not again.
- <i>Cycle suspended due to in--</i>

38
00:04:16.547 --> 00:04:18.800
<i>It was a tragic scene</i>
<i>in Westbrook today</i>

39
00:04:18.883 --> 00:04:19.968
<i>when a corporate convoy</i>

40
00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:22.845
<i>- was ambushed by 6th Street…</i>
- God. Mom.

41
00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:26.224
Morning. <i>mijo</i>.

42
00:04:26.307 --> 00:04:28.059
If you keep sleeping
on the couch like that.

43
00:04:28.142 --> 00:04:30.019
gonna get early onset arthritis.

44
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:32.855
I know. Just dead
after my night shift. is all.

45
00:04:32.939 --> 00:04:36.234
You and the washing machine both.
Forget to re-up it?

46
00:04:36.317 --> 00:04:37.860
Yeah.

47
00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:39.821
I'll take care of it later. 'kay?

48
00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:43.116
Oh. money. right!
You mentioned a wreath update for class.

49
00:04:43.199 --> 00:04:45.076
That happen yet?
When did you say you need it?

50
00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:48.997
No. no. It's fine. Got Doc to handle it.

51
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:53.126
- What do you mean "handle it"?
- I'm good. All set.

52
00:04:53.209 --> 00:04:55.295
Don't go cutting corners. Dee.

53
00:04:55.378 --> 00:04:59.382
Already cashed my paycheck.
You'll get it updated right. Hear me?

54
00:04:59.465 --> 00:05:02.302
Mom. seriously!
Just feed the washer. alright?

55
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:04.762
I forgot this time. I told you.

56
00:05:05.638 --> 00:05:07.473
Promise me you'll buy the update.

57
00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:09.392
Okay. okay.

58
00:05:09.475 --> 00:05:12.312
And you're really going to school
dressed like that?

59
00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:13.563
Uniform’s soaked.

60
00:05:13.646 --> 00:05:15.064
<i>A military-grade implant…</i>

61
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:16.399
- <i>…was found missing from the body</i>
- Hmm?

62
00:05:16.482 --> 00:05:19.402
{\an8}<i>of Lt. Col. James Norris.</i>
<i>shot dead by MaxTac…</i>

63
00:05:19.485 --> 00:05:22.780
{\an8}Mom. you're on TV! Nova!

64
00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:25.658
Not Nova. David. A bloodbath.

65
00:05:25.742 --> 00:05:28.995
- Go on. Off to school.
- Bye.

66
00:05:29.078 --> 00:05:30.621
Love you. <i>mijo</i>.

67
00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:38.421
<i>Maine? It's Gloria.</i>

68
00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:49.015
Hmm…

69
00:05:53.853 --> 00:05:55.521
♪ <i>I ain't your average sicko</i> ♪

70
00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:57.273
♪ <i>I'm dead. just like disco</i> ♪

71
00:05:57.356 --> 00:06:00.735
♪ <i>My bank account</i>
<i>Is zero-zero-zero. oh no</i> ♪

72
00:06:00.818 --> 00:06:02.862
♪ <i>I think I need a hero</i> ♪

73
00:06:02.945 --> 00:06:04.447
♪ <i>I don't have no ego</i> ♪

74
00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:06.616
♪ <i>'Cause I'm spinnin' out now</i> ♪

75
00:06:14.707 --> 00:06:18.127
♪ <i>And now I'm getting older</i>
<i>My heart is growing colder</i> ♪

76
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.963
♪ <i>Oh. that's fine</i> ♪

77
00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:29.263
<i>Trauma Team.</i>
<i>Clear a path immediately.</i>

78
00:06:29.847 --> 00:06:33.101
<i>Emergency evac underway. Emergency evac.</i>

79
00:06:33.184 --> 00:06:35.853
<i>All AVs. vacate the airway.</i>

80
00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:40.274
<i>Trauma Team. Clear a path immediately.</i>
<i>Trauma Team. Clear a path.</i>

81
00:06:40.358 --> 00:06:41.526
<i>Don't walk.</i>

82
00:06:43.194 --> 00:06:44.278
<i>Don't walk.</i>

83
00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:50.034
<i>Walk. Walk. Walk.</i>

84
00:06:50.118 --> 00:06:52.537
<i>Walk. Walk.</i>

85
00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:59.669
♪ <i>And now I'm getting older</i>
<i>My heart is growing colder</i> ♪

86
00:06:59.752 --> 00:07:02.672
♪ <i>Oh. that's fine</i> ♪

87
00:07:03.464 --> 00:07:09.178
{\an8}♪ <i>I was a teenage outlaw</i>
<i>With no worries on my mind</i> ♪

88
00:07:10.346 --> 00:07:13.558
♪ <i>And now I'm getting older</i>
<i>My heart is growing colder</i> ♪

89
00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:15.435
♪ <i>Oh. that's fine</i> ♪

90
00:07:23.693 --> 00:07:27.071
♪ <i>You say it's over</i> ♪

91
00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:30.116
Huh?

92
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:57.768
Good morning to you. class.

93
00:07:57.852 --> 00:08:00.771
Today's attendance. Zero absences.

94
00:08:00.855 --> 00:08:02.440
Martinez. David.

95
00:08:02.523 --> 00:08:05.109
You are not in compliance
with the Academy's dress code.

96
00:08:05.193 --> 00:08:07.111
Yeah. Real sorry about that.

97
00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:09.280
Afraid my uniform's still
at the cleaner's.

98
00:08:09.363 --> 00:08:11.324
Do you have a spare uniform?

99
00:08:11.407 --> 00:08:12.867
Yeah. Spare's there too.

100
00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:16.954
Understood. Please submit
a Uniform Exception form after class.

101
00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:19.290
Now. let us begin today's lesson.

102
00:08:19.373 --> 00:08:22.835
- You will observe…
- <i>Gutter rat. Rat off the street.</i>

103
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:25.421
<i>Me? Nah. Wouldn't show my face.</i>

104
00:08:25.505 --> 00:08:29.091
<i>Cray-crazy. I know.</i>
<i>but some of us here to learn to learn.</i>

105
00:08:29.175 --> 00:08:30.968
<i>With that fossiltech?</i>

106
00:08:31.052 --> 00:08:33.554
<i>Updates. man. Bet it's not compatible.</i>

107
00:08:33.638 --> 00:08:35.556
<i>I made it compatible.</i>

108
00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.475
<i>Huh? How?</i>

109
00:08:37.558 --> 00:08:39.060
<i>How I had to.</i>

110
00:08:39.143 --> 00:08:40.770
<i>Life's gotta be gotta be shit</i>

111
00:08:40.853 --> 00:08:43.314
<i>when a two-bit wreath</i>
<i>costs your life savings.</i>

112
00:08:43.397 --> 00:08:44.232
At this time.

113
00:08:44.315 --> 00:08:47.735
I ask all students
to log into the Green Room for meditation.

114
00:08:47.818 --> 00:08:49.320
Countin’ on ya. Doc.

115
00:08:54.158 --> 00:08:55.576
- <i>Seriously?</i>
- <i>What?</i>

116
00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:57.370
<i>Martinez again!</i>

117
00:08:57.453 --> 00:09:00.831
<i>Not again!</i>

118
00:09:03.834 --> 00:09:06.921
I’m so sorry
for the inconvenience my son has caused.

119
00:09:07.004 --> 00:09:10.299
I wouldn't call this
a matter of money. Mrs. Martinez.

120
00:09:10.383 --> 00:09:14.428
Although I must say it was quite
an expense for us to restore the system.

121
00:09:14.512 --> 00:09:17.223
Of course.
and I will pay for the repairs.

122
00:09:17.306 --> 00:09:18.140
Hmm?

123
00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:21.852
As I understand it.
Mr. Martinez modified his headset

124
00:09:21.936 --> 00:09:25.898
with backalley software
to avoid paying for the licensed update.

125
00:09:25.982 --> 00:09:29.735
This is not behavior befitting a pupil
from a financially stable home.

126
00:09:29.819 --> 00:09:32.863
It's not a problem. really.
We can afford it.

127
00:09:32.947 --> 00:09:34.115
Be that as it may.

128
00:09:34.198 --> 00:09:36.951
I see an opportunity here
to improve David's situation.

129
00:09:37.034 --> 00:09:38.119
Meaning what. exactly?

130
00:09:38.202 --> 00:09:41.080
David is not a good fit
with his classmates.

131
00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:44.500
He could benefit
from a change in environment.

132
00:09:44.584 --> 00:09:47.712
No! Wait. please.
I mean. he has to stay here.

133
00:09:47.795 --> 00:09:51.257
He deserves this education as much
as every other child in this school.

134
00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:54.093
What happened?
Didn't I tell you to get the upgrade?

135
00:09:54.176 --> 00:09:57.305
Yeah. Doc's damn fault.
Gave me a fully borked drive.

136
00:09:57.388 --> 00:09:59.890
You tried to get around
the system. didn't you?

137
00:09:59.974 --> 00:10:02.310
Now. it'll cost us ten times more.

138
00:10:02.393 --> 00:10:03.728
Sorry.

139
00:10:03.811 --> 00:10:05.354
If it's something
you gotta apologize for.

140
00:10:05.438 --> 00:10:07.440
maybe don't do it in the first place. 'ey?

141
00:10:07.523 --> 00:10:09.942
You said you didn't have
the eddies when I asked. so…

142
00:10:10.026 --> 00:10:11.777
I was waiting for payday!

143
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:14.947
You know we don't got that kind of cash
just lying around.

144
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:17.992
Can't you sit still a minute?

145
00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:23.039
You know.
I've been thinkin’ lately.

146
00:10:23.122 --> 00:10:24.540
About what?

147
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:28.169
Maybe I drop out.
Find some work or whatever.

148
00:10:28.252 --> 00:10:29.837
Do you hear yourself?!

149
00:10:29.920 --> 00:10:32.882
C'mon. seriously.
You know we can't afford those repairs.

150
00:10:33.966 --> 00:10:38.679
Plus. you got no idea just how bad
I stand out compared to all of them.

151
00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:42.350
Anyone 'sides a true blue corpo
gets shit on.

152
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:44.352
Even if I do graduate.
they'll never accept me.

153
00:10:44.435 --> 00:10:46.979
No kid from Santo will ever be a suit.

154
00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:48.981
I don't wanna be one anyway.

155
00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:53.778
So. you tell me.

156
00:10:53.861 --> 00:10:56.405
What have I been busting
my ass for then. huh?

157
00:10:57.073 --> 00:11:00.451
Everything I do. I do for you. Dee.

158
00:11:00.534 --> 00:11:01.827
Don't you see that?

159
00:11:01.911 --> 00:11:06.040
You're breaking my heart. <i>mijo</i>.

160
00:11:06.123 --> 00:11:07.124
Wait. What?

161
00:11:07.208 --> 00:11:11.003
My sweet baby boy. So smart. so talented.

162
00:11:11.087 --> 00:11:13.130
You're everything to me.

163
00:11:13.214 --> 00:11:17.051
I want to give you a fighting chance
in this city and a good education.

164
00:11:17.134 --> 00:11:21.931
It's why I put in all of those hours.
Why I'm never home.

165
00:11:24.058 --> 00:11:25.601
Uh. I'm sorry.

166
00:11:26.227 --> 00:11:30.022
Shouldn't have brought it up.
Don't cry. Mom.

167
00:11:30.106 --> 00:11:32.733
Think I don't know
how they treat you?

168
00:11:32.817 --> 00:11:34.735
Think I don't get treated the same way?

169
00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:38.572
But that's why you gotta prove them wrong.

170
00:11:38.656 --> 00:11:40.908
You have to work hard
and rise through the ranks.

171
00:11:40.991 --> 00:11:45.037
My son at Arasaka Tower top floor!
I can just see it.

172
00:11:45.121 --> 00:11:47.581
You've got this. Dee. You're my son.

173
00:11:48.165 --> 00:11:49.875
Yeah. well. easier said than done…

174
00:11:50.459 --> 00:11:52.378
Huh?

175
00:11:55.089 --> 00:11:57.842
Fuck 'em up!

176
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:03.639
- Don't let 'em get away!
- Suit's limo's titanium plated!

177
00:12:03.722 --> 00:12:06.183
The hunt's on. my beastbros!

178
00:12:18.028 --> 00:12:19.572
No one fucks with the Animals!

179
00:12:19.655 --> 00:12:22.199
- Ara-suckers!
- Mom! Brake! Brake hard!

180
00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:23.784
Watch out!

181
00:12:35.087 --> 00:12:37.590
Mom? Mom!

182
00:12:45.389 --> 00:12:48.392
Is that the Trauma Team? Oh. thank Christ.

183
00:12:50.269 --> 00:12:52.646
He's not a client.

184
00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:54.190
Neither is she.

185
00:12:54.273 --> 00:12:55.232
Hey. wait!

186
00:12:55.316 --> 00:12:58.903
Secure the policyholder.
Leave them to the city meat wagons.

187
00:12:58.986 --> 00:13:00.696
- Copy that.
- What?

188
00:13:00.779 --> 00:13:03.449
What the hell? Hey! Where are you going?

189
00:13:04.408 --> 00:13:05.701
Shit!

190
00:13:05.784 --> 00:13:07.703
No way. Just gonna leave us here?

191
00:13:07.786 --> 00:13:10.706
Mom! Momma!

192
00:13:10.789 --> 00:13:12.708
Mom. wake up!

193
00:13:12.791 --> 00:13:14.710
Fucking piece of…

194
00:13:14.793 --> 00:13:19.256
Mom! Dammit. get off me!

195
00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:22.968
Shit. Get the fuck off!
Why won't it-- Damn it!

196
00:13:23.052 --> 00:13:26.013
Mom!

197
00:13:26.096 --> 00:13:27.473
Fuck!

198
00:13:31.435 --> 00:13:33.062
Surgery was a success.

199
00:13:33.145 --> 00:13:36.190
Your mother hasn't come to just yet.
but she's stable.

200
00:13:36.273 --> 00:13:38.400
Need her to stay a few more nights.

201
00:13:38.484 --> 00:13:40.778
Oh. Then. is it okay if I see her?

202
00:13:40.861 --> 00:13:44.532
No can do. buddy.
Visitation ain't part of your package.

203
00:13:44.615 --> 00:13:46.033
Oh. Right.

204
00:13:46.116 --> 00:13:48.994
Anyway. I should get started
on the paperwork.

205
00:13:49.078 --> 00:13:50.496
Brought your mom's things.

206
00:13:50.579 --> 00:13:53.457
And don't forget to zip us those edds.
Got three days.

207
00:13:53.541 --> 00:13:55.042
- Uh…
- Yeah.

208
00:13:55.125 --> 00:13:56.460
There's a reason everyone
in Night City

209
00:13:56.544 --> 00:13:58.128
wants insurance.

210
00:13:58.212 --> 00:13:59.213
Stay safe now.

211
00:13:59.964 --> 00:14:02.466
Yeah. hoops chip. Version back…

212
00:14:03.259 --> 00:14:05.761
Is that all? You low-balling me? Huh?

213
00:14:06.554 --> 00:14:08.764
Nah. forget it. choom.

214
00:14:09.431 --> 00:14:11.350
Dammit! Hmm?

215
00:14:13.936 --> 00:14:15.604
What the fuck?

216
00:14:17.106 --> 00:14:18.732
♪ <i>I ain't your average sicko</i> ♪

217
00:14:18.816 --> 00:14:20.484
♪ <i>I'm dead. just like disco</i> ♪

218
00:14:20.568 --> 00:14:23.028
♪ <i>My bank account</i>
<i>Is zero-zero-zero. oh no</i> ♪

219
00:14:23.112 --> 00:14:24.989
Another account? Christ.

220
00:14:25.072 --> 00:14:28.534
Just enough. She saved so much.
Never knew.

221
00:14:29.243 --> 00:14:31.537
So that would settle the medical…

222
00:14:33.747 --> 00:14:36.500
Still gotta cover rent. Huh?

223
00:14:37.126 --> 00:14:40.754
Doc? Hey. you get the still I sent?
Listen.

224
00:14:40.838 --> 00:14:45.009
Don't think I've forgotten I owe you a
kick in the nuts for that shoddy bootleg.

225
00:14:45.092 --> 00:14:46.594
But check this.

226
00:14:47.219 --> 00:14:48.345
Cyberware.

227
00:14:48.971 --> 00:14:52.808
Yeah. looks. uh. military. doesn't it?

228
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:54.518
How much do you think it'd fetch

229
00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:57.479
if I was interested
and the price was right?

230
00:14:58.272 --> 00:15:00.107
Not selling. Just want an estimate.

231
00:15:03.068 --> 00:15:05.905
Nah. fuck that noise.
No way it's that cheap.

232
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:10.910
Oh. come on. choom.

233
00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:15.039
Whatev! Wasn't selling anyways.

234
00:15:15.122 --> 00:15:18.876
By the way. Don't expect me
to push your XBDs at school anymore!

235
00:15:20.669 --> 00:15:23.422
Enny-pinchin' hack takin' me for a gonk…

236
00:15:24.506 --> 00:15:26.592
A Sandevistan.

237
00:15:26.675 --> 00:15:31.096
No serial number and what?
Military-grade. this thing. really?

238
00:15:31.180 --> 00:15:34.141
It definitely ain't legal. But whatev.

239
00:15:34.224 --> 00:15:36.644
Whoa! The hell are these specs?

240
00:15:49.907 --> 00:15:51.575
Huh? Ah!

241
00:15:56.997 --> 00:15:59.458
Little piece of advice. Martinez.

242
00:15:59.541 --> 00:16:02.378
- Learn to take a hint.
- About what?

243
00:16:02.461 --> 00:16:05.297
Our class.
You're not welcome. Got it?

244
00:16:05.381 --> 00:16:06.924
Huh? If this is about yesterday--

245
00:16:07.007 --> 00:16:09.218
- Who said anything about yesterday?
- What?

246
00:16:09.301 --> 00:16:12.888
You probably figure I give you a hard time
'cause you're poor. Simply untrue.

247
00:16:12.972 --> 00:16:14.974
I'm rather charitably inclined.

248
00:16:15.057 --> 00:16:17.476
Not your fault you were born
on the wrong side of society.

249
00:16:17.559 --> 00:16:20.354
There's no rule
that says a street kid

250
00:16:20.437 --> 00:16:21.855
can't make it at the Academy.

251
00:16:21.939 --> 00:16:23.607
provided they pay their way.

252
00:16:23.691 --> 00:16:26.443
What cracks my chrome
is something else entirely.

253
00:16:26.527 --> 00:16:27.861
- Know what?
- Look. choom.

254
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:30.280
I haven't understood
a single thing coming out of your mouth.

255
00:16:30.364 --> 00:16:31.699
- That right there!
- Hmm…

256
00:16:31.782 --> 00:16:34.451
Time to get gone.
Just drop out. why don't ya?

257
00:16:34.535 --> 00:16:36.662
- Huh?
- You're a misfit. an anomaly.

258
00:16:36.745 --> 00:16:39.957
Human but trash. and there's nothing
that can change that.

259
00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:43.335
Rot in you runs as deep
as your bones. Martinez.

260
00:16:43.419 --> 00:16:46.839
Best you can do
is not spread it to the rest of us.

261
00:16:46.922 --> 00:16:48.465
Did I just short-circ?

262
00:16:48.549 --> 00:16:51.427
Said you didn't care
as long as I paid tuition.

263
00:16:51.510 --> 00:16:53.929
I heard your mommy came in
to see the principal.

264
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:56.223
ask forgiveness for your little stunt.

265
00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:57.516
Caused quite a scene.

266
00:16:57.599 --> 00:17:00.561
crying for her baby boy.
begging for him not to get expelled.

267
00:17:00.644 --> 00:17:01.854
So shameless.

268
00:17:01.937 --> 00:17:04.648
You know. since we're chatting.
I've just always wondered.

269
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:08.110
How could she afford to send you
to Arasaka Academy anyway?

270
00:17:08.193 --> 00:17:11.113
Care to explain. Martinez?

271
00:17:11.697 --> 00:17:15.367
Go on. Tell us.
How does mommy pay your way?

272
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:17.745
What's any Night City bottom-feeder.

273
00:17:17.828 --> 00:17:19.872
do to make a quick eurobuck. huh?

274
00:17:19.955 --> 00:17:23.500
Oh! A couple of pretty
salacious things come to mind.

275
00:17:23.584 --> 00:17:24.626
Tired of this shit.

276
00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:27.629
- Hold on. choom. Who said we were done?
- Fuck off!

277
00:17:36.930 --> 00:17:40.267
Huh? Oh? What?

278
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:43.604
Huh? Ha!

279
00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:51.487
Got anything slotted? MMA freeware maybe?

280
00:17:51.570 --> 00:17:56.492
Hmm? Hmm. Aww!

281
00:18:16.720 --> 00:18:18.055
Knew it.

282
00:18:18.138 --> 00:18:23.018
Nothing like the Strongarms 400 to bring
out the best in your kung-fu chipware.

283
00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:25.395
Organic knuckles? Seriously?

284
00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:29.024
Wanna try me again?
I suggest you pack some serious chrome.

285
00:18:29.108 --> 00:18:30.943
Or just drop out.

286
00:18:31.026 --> 00:18:33.529
You know what I'd prefer.

287
00:18:38.951 --> 00:18:41.578
<i>Mr. Martinez?</i>

288
00:18:42.412 --> 00:18:46.166
<i>I'm calling in regards</i>
<i>to Gloria Martinez's condition.</i>

289
00:18:46.834 --> 00:18:49.211
- Huh?
- She was stable this morning.

290
00:18:49.294 --> 00:18:52.673
but then her vitals began to nosedive
really out of nowhere.

291
00:18:52.756 --> 00:18:57.553
But you said the surgery was successful.

292
00:18:57.636 --> 00:19:00.973
True. But only so much
we can do on the discount package.

293
00:19:01.056 --> 00:19:04.143
Worn down as she was.
I doubt she'd have lasted much longer.

294
00:19:04.226 --> 00:19:06.186
Overworked. seemed to me.

295
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:09.439
Anyway. I'm supposed to tell you
we offer some burial options.

296
00:19:09.523 --> 00:19:12.818
People in Night City
want corpo gigs for a reason. kid.

297
00:19:13.610 --> 00:19:16.822
<i>Greetings. valued</i>
<i>customer. We are sorry for your loss.</i>

298
00:19:16.905 --> 00:19:18.866
<i>To ease things at this difficult time.</i>

299
00:19:18.949 --> 00:19:21.034
<i>we can deliver the body</i>
<i>of your dearly departed</i>

300
00:19:21.118 --> 00:19:23.203
<i>to your home or to a funeral home.</i>

301
00:19:23.287 --> 00:19:24.454
<i>Would you like to learn more?</i>

302
00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:26.081
I got a choice?

303
00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:28.750
<i>Is our budget-friendly</i>
<i>cremation service right for you?</i>

304
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:32.921
<i>Waive those pesky delivery fees</i>
<i>and bring your loved one home today.</i>

305
00:19:41.013 --> 00:19:42.139
<i>Don't walk.</i>

306
00:19:42.222 --> 00:19:43.891
- <i>Good day. Mrs. Martinez.</i>
<i>- Don't walk.</i>

307
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.475
- <i>We've received a quote for the repairs</i>
- <i>Don't walk.</i>

308
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:47.102
- <i>to our system infrastructure.</i>
- <i>Don't walk.</i>

309
00:19:47.186 --> 00:19:50.606
<i>As agreed. I've sent you an e-mail</i>
<i>with the payment details.</i>

310
00:19:50.689 --> 00:19:52.441
<i>Also. perhaps you've had time to think?</i>

311
00:19:52.524 --> 00:19:53.734
{\an8}<i>Do let me know.</i>

312
00:19:53.817 --> 00:19:55.819
{\an8}<i>Just say the word</i>
<i>and we'll begin making arrangements</i>

313
00:19:55.903 --> 00:19:58.280
{\an8}<i>for David's transfer</i>
<i>to another institution.</i>

314
00:19:58.363 --> 00:20:00.699
<i>Please note.</i>
<i>To maintain your utilities contract.</i>

315
00:20:00.782 --> 00:20:03.452
<i>you must pay a penalty of 500 eurodollars</i>

316
00:20:03.535 --> 00:20:07.331
<i>in addition to any past</i>
<i>due amounts and late fees.</i>

317
00:20:07.414 --> 00:20:09.333
<i>If you cannot pay by the deadline.</i>

318
00:20:09.416 --> 00:20:12.920
<i>your services will be terminated</i>
<i>in the following order…</i>

319
00:20:13.003 --> 00:20:15.672
<i>Trauma Team.</i>
<i>Clear a path immediately.</i>

320
00:20:15.756 --> 00:20:17.799
- <i>…medical…</i>
- <i>Ding-ding. Martinez!</i>

321
00:20:17.883 --> 00:20:19.885
<i>Me again. Time's up.</i>

322
00:20:19.968 --> 00:20:22.179
<i>Rent's long past due.</i>

323
00:20:22.262 --> 00:20:24.848
<i>Keep this shit up</i>
<i>and I won't just change your lock.</i>

324
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:27.935
<i>I'll throw your ass out</i>
<i>on the street. You feel me?</i>

325
00:20:28.018 --> 00:20:30.187
♪ <i>City burn</i> ♪

326
00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:35.359
♪ <i>We're not planning to return</i> ♪

327
00:20:35.442 --> 00:20:38.695
♪ <i>Trying so hard to be free</i> ♪

328
00:20:44.284 --> 00:20:47.746
The implant I showed you.
you said you'd take it off me for 10K?

329
00:20:48.830 --> 00:20:51.208
Six now? Said ten yesterday. choom!

330
00:20:51.291 --> 00:20:53.335
Come on. That's just one fucking day.

331
00:20:53.418 --> 00:20:55.587
And we both know that it's worth way more!

332
00:20:55.671 --> 00:20:57.839
Hell yeah. I looked into it. and I--

333
00:21:00.425 --> 00:21:03.512
Oh. yeah? Well. fuck you too! Bitch.

334
00:21:09.309 --> 00:21:12.312
<i>Katsuo here. I heard about your mom.</i>

335
00:21:12.396 --> 00:21:16.066
<i>I'd offer my sympathies.</i>
<i>but find it hard to sympathize.</i>

336
00:21:16.149 --> 00:21:17.818
<i>God only knows what she had to endure</i>

337
00:21:17.901 --> 00:21:21.238
<i>to send her delinquent son to an Academy</i>
<i>he doesn't belong at.</i>

338
00:21:21.989 --> 00:21:24.408
<i>Her methods couldn't have been noble</i>

339
00:21:24.491 --> 00:21:28.537
<i>if she died in a car accident. So mundane.</i>

340
00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:29.663
<i>But you know?</i>

341
00:21:29.746 --> 00:21:32.749
<i>Karma. There's a lesson in this. David.</i>

342
00:21:34.084 --> 00:21:37.587
<i>Your mother tried to live</i>
<i>beyond her means and died.</i>

343
00:21:37.671 --> 00:21:39.006
<i>Don't make the same mistake.</i>

344
00:21:52.436 --> 00:21:55.480
{\an8}-

345
00:21:55.564 --> 00:21:57.607
Christ. The hell. Who is that?

346
00:21:58.275 --> 00:22:00.610
Aah. David. hey.

347
00:22:01.945 --> 00:22:03.739
That the big bad Sandy?

348
00:22:03.822 --> 00:22:07.326
Not a badge or fixer in town
who's not looking for that beaut.

349
00:22:07.409 --> 00:22:09.119
I told you though…

350
00:22:09.202 --> 00:22:13.040
ain't gonna find anyone sane
willing to take it off your hands.

351
00:22:13.123 --> 00:22:15.625
I'm not here to sell.

352
00:22:15.709 --> 00:22:20.130
I want this fused here.
High time I chromed the fuck up.

353
00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:32.768
{\an8}

354
00:22:39.316 --> 00:22:45.155
♪ <i>Eyes. burning a way through me</i> ♪

355
00:22:45.822 --> 00:22:51.328
♪ <i>Eyes. destroying so sweetly</i> ♪

356
00:22:52.245 --> 00:22:57.876
♪ <i>Now. there's a fire in me</i> ♪

357
00:22:57.959 --> 00:23:04.424
♪ <i>A fire that burns</i> ♪

358
00:23:31.993 --> 00:23:34.663
♪ <i>This fire is out of control</i> ♪

359
00:23:34.746 --> 00:23:38.542
♪ <i>I'll burn it. I'll burn it</i> ♪

360
00:23:48.009 --> 00:23:52.430
♪ <i>I'll burn it. I'll burn it</i> ♪

360
